name: stac-vrt
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "stac-vrt" %}
{% set version = "1.0.3" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/stac_vrt-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: dc114961c3de51f5ed331c4f26e7618a8afed1da0c47bfb9135b0208db094c5e

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m flit install

requirements:
  host:
    - flit
    - python >=3.7
  run:
    - affine
    - numpy
    - pyproj
    - python >=3.7
    - rasterio

test:
  imports:
    - stac_vrt
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://pypi.org/project/stac_vrt/
  summary: Quickly build a GDAL VRT from a STAC Item Collection.
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - TomAugspurger
